        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 5 at 1:50PM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 149 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Strongsville, or 10 miles north of Medina, moving northwest at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cleveland, Lorain, Elyria, Medina, Parma, Strongsville, Brunswick,
Westlake, North Royalton, North Ridgeville, Avon Lake, Amherst,
Grafton, North Olmsted, Avon, Parma Heights, Rocky River, Brook Park,
Berea, and Fairview Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
